    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@wski thanks for taking a look here! As I said, I don't think that anything in the documentation actually will use `assert()`. `require()` should be used if you are checking the input or whether a user is allowed to do something or whether the contract is in the correct state to do something. You should use assert for e.g. checking that the state of the contract will never be set to something invalid.",
